cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.EC, cs.CY, cs.CL 

This paper primarily focuses on optimizing search experiences in two-sided marketplaces, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as ranking and relevance. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of policy learners, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (ML) and specifically reinforcement learning (RL), making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. The paper also addresses the competing business metrics that e-commerce companies typically tackle, which falls under the sub-category of computational economics (cs.EC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of constraints and optimization techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CY) and computational linguistics (cs.CL), respectively.
